BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: tell application "Reminders"	set activeReminders to name of (reminders of list "Reminders" whose completed is false)	if activeReminders is not {} then		return first item of activeReminders	else		return ""	end ifend tell

BTTAdditionalActions.BTTInlineAppleScript: activate application "Activity Monitor"tell application "System Events"	tell process "Activity Monitor"		tell radio button "CPU" of radio group 1 of group 2 of toolbar 1 of window 1 to perform action "AXPress"	end tellend tell

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: set cpu to do shell script "ps axo %cpu | awk '{s+=$1}END{print s}'"return cpu & "%"

BTTAdditionalActions.BTTInlineAppleScript: activate application "Activity Monitor"tell application "System Events"	tell process "Activity Monitor"		tell radio button "Memory" of radio group 1 of group 2 of toolbar 1 of window 1 to perform action "AXPress"	end tellend tell

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: set mem to do shell script "ps -A -o %mem | awk '{s+=$1}END{print s}'"return mem & "%"

do shell script "pmset -g batt | grep InternalBattery | column -t"set x to the resultset percentage to word 6 of xset state to word 7 of xset t1 to word 8 of xset t2 to word 9 of xset remaining to the word 10 of xif remaining contains "remaining" then	if state is "discharging" then		return "⬇" & percentage & "% | " & t1 & ":" & t2 & " remaining"	else if state is "charging" then		return "⬆" & percentage & "% | " & t1 & ":" & t2	else		return percentage	end ifelse	return percentageend if

BTTAdditionalActions.BTTPredefinedActionName: Close currently open Touch Bar group

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "Safari" is running then	tell application "Safari"		repeat with t in tabs of windows			tell t				if URL starts with "http://www.youtube.com/watch" or URL starts with "https://www.youtube.com/watch" then					return text 1 thru -11 of (name of t as text)				end if			end tell		end repeat	end tellend ifreturn ""

BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)
BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: if application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes" to playpauseend if

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		try			set whatshappening to (get player state as string)		end try				if whatshappening = "playing" then			return "pause"		else			return "play"		end if			end tellelse	return ""end if

BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Open URL / Open URL With Selection

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: # https://itunes.apple.com/ru/app/json-helper-for-applescript/id453114608?l=en&mt=12# https://itunes.apple.com/ru/app/location-helper-for-applescript/id488536386?mt=12tell application "Location Helper"	set clocation_coords to get location coordinates	tell application "JSON Helper"		set weather to fetch JSON from "http://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?lat=" & item 1 of clocation_coords & "&lon=" & item 2 of clocation_coords & "&units=metric&appid=..."		set temp to temp of main of weather as string				set defDel to AppleScript's text item delimiters		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to "-"		set newname to text items of temp		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to "−"		set the temp to (newname as string)		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to defDel				set cond_icon to icon of item 1 of weather of weather as string				if cond_icon is in ["01d", "01n"] then			set cond to "☀"		else if cond_icon is in ["02d", "02n", "03d", "03n", "04d", "04n"] then			set cond to "☁"		else if cond_icon is in ["09d", "09n", "10d", "10n"] then			set cond to "☂"		else if cond_icon is in ["11d", "11n"] then			set cond to "☈"		else if cond_icon is in ["13d", "13n"] then			set cond to "☃"		else if cond_icon is in ["50d", "50n"] then			set cond to "♨"		else			set cond to ""		end if				return cond & " " & (temp as integer) & "°C"	end tellend tell

if application "Safari" is running then	tell application "Safari"		repeat with t in tabs of windows			tell t				if URL starts with "https://vk.com/audios" or URL starts with "https://vk.com/music" then					return name of t as text				end if			end tell		end repeat	end tellend ifreturn ""

BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)
BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: if application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is playing then			next track		end if	end tellend if

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: #!/usr/bin/env osascriptif application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is playing then			return (get artist of current track) & " — " & (get name of current track)		end if	end tellend ifreturn ""

BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)
BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: if application "iTerm" is running then	tell application "iTerm"		activate		tell last window			select		end tell	end tellelse	tell application "iTerm"		activate		tell application "System Events"			keystroke return using {command down}		end tell	end tellend if
